# README Synchronization Rule

When you modify any CRUX tool-related files, update `README.md` to reflect those changes.

## Tool-Related Files (trigger README update)
- `CRUX.md` - specification changes
- `AGENTS.md` - agent awareness block changes
- `.cursor/rules/_CRUX-RULE.mdc` - always-applied rule changes
- `.cursor/agents/crux-cursor-rule-manager.md` - subagent changes
- `.cursor/commands/crux-compress.md` - command changes
- `.cursor/hooks/detect-crux-changes.sh` - hook script changes
- `.cursor/hooks.json` - hook configuration changes
- `CRUX-Utils` skill - utility skill changes (token estimation, checksums)

## Excluded Files (do NOT trigger README update)
- `.gitignore`, `.editorconfig`, and other generic config files
- Test files, temporary files, or generated `.crux.mdc` outputs
- Files unrelated to CRUX tool functionality

## Update Guidelines
1. Keep README sections synchronized with the corresponding component documentation
2. Update diagrams if workflow or architecture changes
3. Update file location tables if paths change
4. Update usage examples if command syntax or options change
5. Preserve README structure - make surgical updates, don't rewrite entire sections
